	abstract = {Describing mathematically, the intensity duration curves of electrostimulation by hyperbolas, Lapicque introduced two terms which characterized the functional relationship: “Rheobose” was the lowest intensify with indefinite pulse duration which just stimulated muscles or nerves. “Chronaxie” was that pulse duration at which the threshold intensity was twice that of the rheobase. Up to now, both terms have never played an important role in cardiac pacing.
