                  Pacing with constant current needs twice that pulse duration of constant voltage stimulation.
                
                
                  Smaller electrodes are more favorable because the pulse duration they need may be reduced without losing safety.
                
                
                  Estimation of the safety margin with decreasing output of the generator or with programmable pulse duration is possible if the chronaxie of a specific electrode is known.},
